1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the analysis and design of error-correcting codes, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Inactivation decoding is a technique used in network coding, which is a subfield of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the tradeoff between decoding complexity and failure probability, which is a common problem in the design of algorithms and data structures. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may be relevant to the study of network coding in social and information networks. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper touches upon the complexity of decoding LT and Raptor codes, which may be of interest to researchers in computational complexity.
